{"key":"processedPost-9423338","value":{"id":9423338,"first":9423224,"last":9538696,"when":1229184854,"utime":"12/13/08 06:14 PM","content":"Corn cobs make a great bulk substrate material.&nbsp; You don't even have to break them up.&nbsp; I've often saved all the corn cobs after a BBQ, and then they can be laid down in a tray and spawned with grains or brf cakes.&nbsp; Best results come when you embed them in manure or coir.&nbsp; Don't forget to pasteurize, and make sure there's no corn kernels stuck to the cobs.&nbsp; The animal bedding will probably work too.<br />RR","title":"Re: Corn Cob (Animal bedding litter) the experiment.","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}